-- Hungarian Forint Pares Declines as Greek Politicians Reach Deal
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-02-09T14:11:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/hungarian-forint-pares-declines-as-greek-politicians-reach-deal.html
The forint pared losses after Greek
political leaders struck a deal on a package of austerity
measures, clearing the way for the country’s second rescue in
two years.  Hungary’s currency was down 0.2 percent to 290.8 per euro
by 3:07 p.m. in Budapest, after depreciating as much as 0.9
percent earlier today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
